Chapter 8   Asking for Sightseeing Information 第八章  觀光資訊 談論旅遊勝地 
1. I’m wondering if you can recommend some good sightseeing spots?我想你是否能推薦些觀光勝地給我?2. Are you interested in shopping, historic sights or scenic spots?你對逛街購物,歷史遺跡,或風景區有沒有興趣?3. Oh, I would say a little of everything.哦,每種都有點興趣.4. There are some excellent sights in the walking distance from here.從這裡走一段路就有一些很棒的風景區.5. Do you have a map of this area?你有這地區的地圖嗎?6. We also have some brochures about the sights.我們還有觀光手冊。 
報名參加旅遊 1. Can you help us arrange a bus tour?你能幫我安排一個巴士旅遊嗎?2. You bet. Where would you like to go?當然！您要到哪裡呢?3. Do you have the two-day tour to Las Vegas the day after tomorrow?你們後天有辦拉斯維加斯二日遊嗎?4. What time does the bus leave, and where do we catch it?巴士幾點開？我們要在哪兒上車?5. The bus leaves at a quarter past six in the morning.  巴士會在早上六點十五分開車. 6. It will pick you up at your hotel.它會到飯店載你們.
購買紀念品 1. How much is this Mickey Mouse cap?請問這頂米老鼠帽多少錢?2. This cap is twenty dollars.帽子一頂二十元.3. Oh, boy! They are expensive!天啊!怎麼那麼貴!4. Mickey Mouse’s face glows in the dark.米老鼠的臉在黑暗中會發光.5. Well, in that case, how can I go wrong?嗯,這樣的話,我怎麼能不買呢?6. Would you like it gift-wrapped?要當作禮物包起來嗎?
拍照 1. Would you mind taking pictures for us?你能幫我們拍照嗎?2. Just stand over there.站在那裡就行了。 3. Can you get the Empire State Building in?你能不能把整棟帝國大廈拍進去?4. Move back a little bit. Say cheese!往後退一點點。微笑!5. Could you take another one, please?可以幫我們再拍一張嗎?6. You’ve got it. Move in a little closer.好啊。靠近一點.
實用字彙 1. wonder                         想知道 2. recommend          推薦 3. sightseeing spot    觀光勝地 4. historic spot          歷史遺跡 5. scenic spot            風景區 6. excellent                       很棒的 7. distance                        距離 8. brochure                       小冊子 9. arrange                         安排 10. You bet.                      當然 11. the day after tomorrow      後天 12. quarter                        四分之一;一刻鐘 13. pick up                       搭載,以車子接 14. cap   帽子 15.glow                            發光 16.dark                              黑暗;暗處 17. gift-wrapped   禮品包裝的 18. take pictures               拍照 19. perfect                        完美的 20. You’ve got it.             好啊 

Chapter 9   Bargaining第九章  討價還價 購買商品時議價 1. Could you bring the price down?可以算便宜一點嗎?2. It’s worth every penny of it.物超所值。 3. That’s too expensive..太貴了。 4. What price range do you have in mind?你心中理想價錢是多少？.5. Lower the price, and I’ll consider it.價錢低一點我就會考慮。 6. It’s just five dollars over your limit它只超過你的預算五元。 
與店員議價I 1. Do you have any discount?你們有任何折扣嗎?2. The price is fixed.我們都照定價。 3. It’s a little overpriced.標價有點貴。 4. We don’t have anything less expensive.我們沒有更便宜的。 5. That’s unreasonable.這真是賣得太貴了。 6. It’s a clearance sale.這是清倉大拍賣。 
與店員議價II 1. That’s more than I want to spend.比我想得還要貴 2. It’s the cheapest one in our store.它是我們店裡最便宜的.3. I’d buy this if it were cheaper.再便宜一點我就買 4. I can give you 5% off.我可以給你打95折 5. I can’t afford it.我付不起.6. Never mind.沒有關係. 
與店員議價III 1. That’s .very nice. I’ll take it.看起來不錯、我就買這個 2. I’ll wrap it up for you. 我將為你包裝起來 3. Can I pay by credit card or by cash?我要用信用卡或現金付帳?4. Okay, now you’ll need to sign here.好,現在你需要在這裡簽名。 5. If it’s not suitable. Could I have a refund on this?假如不適合。我能否退貨？ 6. No problem.沒有問題。 
實用字彙 1.bring down             使(價格)下跌 2.price                  價格 3.worth                價值的 4.penny               一分硬幣 5.expensive              太貴 6.consider              考慮 7.limit                   預算 8.discount                打折 9.fixed                      固定的 10.overprice              定價過高 11.unreasonable        不合理的 12.clearance              清倉 13.cheapest               最便宜的 14.afford                 力足夠---做---15.wrap up               包起來 16.credit card           信用卡 17.sign (v.)               簽名 18.cash                     現金 19.refund                         退貨 20.suitable                適合的 
